## ✅ Why Redux Toolkit is Better than Old Redux ❓

| Old Redux         | Redux Toolkit   |
| ----------------- | --------------- |
| Boilerplate heavy | Minimal code    |
| Manual actions    | Auto‑generated  |
| Switch statements | Slice reducers  |
| Error‑prone       | Safe with Immer |

***

## ✅ Interview‑Ready One‑Liner ✅

> **A slice in Redux Toolkit is a combination of state, reducers, and actions created using `createSlice` to reduce boilerplate and simplify Redux logic.**

***

## ✅ Best Practices ⭐

✔ One slice per feature  
✔ Keep slices small  
✔ Use `createAsyncThunk` for API calls  
✔ Don’t put component logic in slices

